Compile options and module requirement on Summit-Dev
*** 
    *If using pgi compiler, load cuda/9.0.69
    *If using gcc compiler, load cuda (default version)
    *If using ibm compiler, load cuda/9.0.69

(1) CUDA Fortran; use pgi (so that AMREX_CUDA_FORT_DEVICE is expanded to be attributes(device))
    USE_CUDA = TRUE

(2) CUDA/OpenACC; use pgi
    USE_CUDA = TRUE
    USE_ACC  = TRUE
    USE_OMP_OFFLOAD = FALSE

(3) CUDA/OpenMP; use ibm xl
    USE_CUDA = TRUE
    USE_ACC  = FALSE
    USE_OMP_OFFLOAD = TRUE
